text: Margaux Le Mouël (born 8 August 2001) is a French professional footballer who plays as a forward for Division 1 Féminine club Guingamp. ==Career== A native of Loudéac, Le Mouël began playing youth football with local side Loudéac OSC. A youth academy graduate of Guingamp, and after suffering a serios knee injury in late 2017, Le Mouël made her professional debut on 4 May 2019, coming on as a substitute for Ekaterina Tyryshkina in a 1–1 draw against Paris Saint- Germain. Le Mouël is a French youth international and was part of the France under-19 squad which won 2019 UEFA Championship. ==References== Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:People from Pontivy Category:Sportspeople from Morbihan Category:Footballers from Brittany Category:French women's footballers Category:Women's association football forwards Category:En Avant de Guingamp (women) players Category:Division 1 Féminine players
